description: Continuing Bruce Zick's epic story of Atlas and his struggle with the Pantheon of Gods, Atlas battles the monster, Sh'en Chui, and eventually defeats it with the help of GoldenRod. As it turns out, this is just the first in a series of battles Atlas will have to face in order to secure earth from the wrath of his enemies. In this issue, we also see the creation of Atlas' idyllic Mythic Oasis, the return of his arch-nemesis, Bol, from a millennia-long hibernation, the revelation of the Seven Mythic Wonders, and our first glimpse at the ethereal home of the Gods -- Eternia. Eventually, though, the most troubling aspect of Atlas' banishment to earth becomes readily evident -- GoldenRod is losing power!

Overview

In the midst of a perilous "Paradise Detour," Luke continues his hunt for the missing S'ybll, while being pursued by what appears to be his old foe, the Night Beast. Eventually, the mystery of the successive unexplained appearances of Tanith Shire, the Night Beast, and Ben Kenobi is solved... and as it turns out, S'ybll has some very sinister -- and selfish -- plans for the young Jedi. Needless to say, Luke escapes S'ybll's clutches, after another Rebel rescue just in the nick of time. He, along with our other Rebel heroes, finally arrive at the new Rebel base on Hoth, ready for "A New Beginning." They're greeted there by a perturbed Princess Leia, who, before they can so much as look around, has another potentially dangerous mission for the unflappable Luke, Han, and Chewie.
name: The Paradise Detour (part 2), A New Beginning (part 1)

description:
Overview

What kind of effect will Gunk have on Professor Palmenter? Find out in this issue. Meanwhile, Cal experiences the aftereffects of last issue's attack by one of the alien rulers of earth... an apology? Back in time, young Cal and Connie begin to experiment with their new powers. Then, apology or not, Cal and Terri make a desperate escape attempt which ends in a bang!

In the Torch of Liberty back-up feature, more of the origin of the flag-wielding defender of American justice is revealed.
name: The Phoenix Agenda Part 3; Metamorphosis

description:
Overview

On the lava flow the Spaniards called El Malpais, Enoch Nakai fought his own demon, in Predator: Big Game. But though the Beast is dead, Enoch's demons aren't, and he is destined to meet with them again in "Predator: Blood on Two-Witch Mesa," featuring a premiere script by Terry LaBan and beautifully detailed art by Howard Cobb.

Also in Dark Horse Comics #20, we present part 2 of "X: Welcome to the Jungle," by Eric Luke and Nghia Lam. Wellman's a good cop, probably the only one left in Arcadia. But in this web of politics, deceit, and murder, the only way out may be to cross that line and become what he hates the most -- a creature like X!

Hermes and the Eyeball Kid take to the air in a climactic battle above the streets while Joe Theseus and Rosario beat the snot out of each other in the midst of the Patterns of Fate.

The buoy has been found, but the reward money goes to the person who turns it over -- not the person who finds it. In part 2 of "Buoy 77," one treachery leads to another over the promised reward -- an unbelievable fortune to the citizens of Vi√ßosa, Brazil. The essence of realistic superheroes has been distilled and Stephen Itner demonstrates its potency in his hilarious story "The Legion of Justice." With great pleasure, we present Rick Geary's "Just Folks," a revealing description of many strange and unusual people we're all too embarrassed to admit knowing, and "Close Calls," a testimonial of fateful proportions.

Chapters

  • Hermes vs. The Eyeball Kid - Part 7, "Lo, There SHall Come a Smack in the Chops."
  • Close Calls
  • Buoy 77 - Part 2
  • Just Folks
  • The Legion of Justice
name: Hermes vs. The Eyeball Kid; Close Calls; Buoy 77; Just Folks; The Legion of Justice

description: Things continue to get weirder as Hellboy, the World's Greatest Paranormal Investigator, continues his search for clues to the mystery of the lost arctic expedition and the secret behind the strange vampire frog creature he battled in his first issue. The mystery deepens inside the crumbling walls of an ancient mansion where we meet Hellboy's partners, Abe Sapien and Liz Sherman. Also featuring chapter two in the amazing origin of Monkeyman and O'Brien, where Axwell Tiberius comes to the heartbreaking realization that he may never again be able to go home.
name: Chapter Two

first_appearance_teams.name: Bureau for Paranormal Research and Defense

team_credits.name: Bureau for Paranormal Research and Defense

description: This is it! The all-new, all-exciting, bimonthly continuing series makes its triumphant return to the racks! Thrilling stories, brilliant art -- this is the one, folks! The comic-book event of the decade! In fact, this is the comic-book series you'll be telling your grandkids about. This first issue begins with a six-page introduction that finds Frank (a.k.a. Madman) having his brain waves recorded, explaining much of what's gone on in the previous series. Then, the main story, "Crash Course for the Ravers," involves creatures from outer space who crash into the outskirts of Snap City as local street beatniks are altered by an unknown element found in the city's sewers. Madman's world contains robots, aliens, mad scientists, and monsters. This comic boasts the best of action-adventure, science fiction, mystery, and romance. Thirty-two pages of cover-to-cover comics, and a splendid color back cover by none other than Frank Miller (Sin City)!
name: Crash Course for the Ravers

description:
This is it! The final confrontation between the Shadow and the "Leviathan," the strange beast that has been stalking the sewers and terrorizing the city! And oh what a battle it is!

And that's not all -- hop on this train and you'll see such sights as the secret of Professor Medsker's laboratory, the real leader of the jewel thief gang, and the final fate of Wainright, Sister Ellen, and Frankie Ross. Prepare to be surprised and amazed!¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†

volume.name: The Shadow: In the Coils of Leviathan

description: In the Star Wars galaxy, automatons are so much necessary property, but even first-degree droids are considered expendable! Set before the events of Star Wars: A New Hope and the formation of the Empire, Droids features the adventures of protocol droid See-Threepio and astromech droid Artoo-Detoo in the Kalarba system. Despite their differences, See-Threepio and Artoo-Detoo know that the best way to survive is to stick together. Thank the maker!

X has straddled the fence of justice for too long, and now the forces of "justice" in Arcadia are out to take him in. Don't think that the local constables are dumb enough to just send out an APB, action fans -- Arcadia law enforcement likes assault helicopters, automatic weapons, and some rather¬†enhanced¬†patrolmen!

As his war on those who oppose him escalates, so does the property damage, and you can bet X will take that war to where it will hurt his enemies the most. Guest starring the Pit Bulls, you'll have no doubts as to why this issue is entitled "Big Guns"!
name: Big Guns

description:
While the clones in Metropolis continue to deteriorate, Superman's growth is now also out of control. Plus, Lois Lane writes a scathing condemnation of Lex Luthor for the Daily Planet.

Notes:

  • Eradicator cameo flashback appearance.
  • "DC Universe 16" one page text piece featuring "What is TV Like in the DC Universe?" and "DCTV Spotlight". Green Lantern artwork by ??? Banks and Romeo Tanghal. This month's feature has the appearance of a TV Guide page format. It features the time, channel, show, a brief summary of the episode and who is starring in it.
  • Triangle 1994 #15.
  • Chronological continuation from Superman #88.
  • Chronological continuation in Action Comics #698.
name: Collision Course

description: As Damien begins to question his trust in him, Crassus, the mysterious Un-Man, vanishes. Meanwhile, Damien and his new companion, Scylla, are carted off to a depraved exhibition.
name: Blue Skies of Purgatory

volume.name: American Freak: A Tale of the Un-Men

description: The Baker family begins to unravel in the face of Maxine's fate. Ellen leaves the farm, Buddy wanders into Annie's tepee. Cliff is seized by paroxysms of terror at his sister's grave site.
name: A Strange And Reckless Freedom

description: The Dark Knight and Ballistic join forces to battle a murderous trio trying to kill Abattoir.
name: Malevolent Maniaxe

description: Stopped in his tracks with fear, Batman has to discover why a particular shape is causing him to be paralyzed.
name: Troubled Dreams

description: Heartbroken over the death of someone close, Black Orchid is led by a tribal elder to an ancient magical site in the Brazilian rain forest in a quest for her identity. ¬†
name: Clicks And Silence Frogs And Mahogany

description:
Damage is a reluctant young hero possessing devastating power beyond his wildest imaginings-a teenager capable of totaling a car with one punch, or leveling buildings for blocks around. But how he acquired these powers is a disturbing mystery. And if that's not enough, after Damage's powers first surface, Superman's old adversary, the giant cyborg Metallo, appears on the scene to test the youth's powers!

Grant Emerson has a system of five rules. These rules help him make the most of his life despite moving from school to school constantly.

But none of his rules will help him escape from the mercenary supervillain Metallo. Maybe his newfound powers will.
name: Damage

first_appearance_locations.name: Stryker's Island Maximum Security Internment Center

location_credits.name: Stryker's Island Maximum Security Internment Center

description: In part 3 of the 5-part 'The Teiresias Wars,' Cliff Steele gets a new body - one designed to his specifications. Meanwhile, the Doom Patrol learns the origin of the Teiresias Wars, as their home is under siege by the Builders, the group seeking to recreate the Tower of Babel.
name: The Teiresia's Wars part 3:The Witness Trees

description: The gluttonous Gross National Product and his emaciated sidekick Def Izzit take on the Fighting American and the Washington Establishment in a tale of greed, excess spending and dirty economics that leaves the nation reeling...because when it comes to these guys, somebody's going to pay. ¬†
name: No Hope For Misanthropes

description: Flash goes on trial for negligence in "Swift Decision". Part 2 of 3, continued from the previous issue. Story continues next issue.
name: Swift Decision

description: Jack T. Chance vs. Lobo. Unfortunately the Main Man knows of the yellow weakness!
name: The Book of Endings!

description: Part 2 of the 2-part "King of the Netherworld." Mongrel, shaken by the accidental death of Mustang Suzy, continues his iron-handed lordship over Chicago's outcast metahumans. Hawkman is forced into a no-holds-barred battle with this New Blood character to prevent further deaths...and avert an all-out war. ¬†
name: King of The Netherworld, Part 2

description:
Captain Atom and the Ray rally the Justice League against Dreamslayer, who's backed by a mysterious cosmic power and who claims to be the entity the cult has been trying to reach.

In this issue Booster gold gets one of his many different robot looking costumes. They kept changing for a while after Doomsday destroyed the first one.

Dreamslayer has become more powerful and escapes from a machine with the help of a misguided Randolph. The battle is still going on at the end of the issue. Dreamslayer zaps Ice and it is left open ended as to how this has hurt her.

Also in this issue, T.O. Morrow visits Max Lord to warn him about the future and Amazing Man visits his dying grandfather to talk about their past.
name: Cult of the Machine, Part II: God in the Machine

description: Following an attack by a mysterious band of metahuman villains, the JLI tracks its foes to a hidden fortress in Africa, where the League discovers an apocalyptic cult bent on the destruction of the modern world. ¬†
name: Visions of Death

description: Part 2 of the 3-part 'Purification Plague.' The Task Force's mission to infiltrate the group of military survivalists is compromised when one of the heroes is recognized. But if the Task Force fails, a virus will be released that could wipe out half the population of Earth.¬† ¬†
name: The Purification Plague, Part 2: Children of Ignorance

description:
Invisible Kid gets a taste of what his teammates suffered at Kid Psycho's hands as another group of Legionnaires become fugitives in the Paris Dome.

Matter-Eater Lad is transformed into a woman so he and Kono can infiltrate a group of Sklarian pirates who have been stealing food rations from starving people on Earth.
name: Chain Gang

description:
The Spoiler keeps tabs on the Electrocutioner and Czonk, while Robin braces for the inevitable as the air runs out in the armored car that he and the Cluemaster are trapped in!

Robin and Cluemaster trapped. Luckily, other villains return to get the cash and inadvertently rescue them. Spoiler knocks out Cluemaster and it seems she has developed a crush on Robin.
name: Last Gasps

description: Even as his relationship with Dian Belmont ignites, Wesley Dodds must contend with dark dreams of brutal murders - handsome young socialites found completely drained of blood.
name: The Vamp: Act One

description:
The identity of young Daniel's mysterious abductor is revealed, and Lyta receives some news that sends her down a dark path that will have dire consequences for the Dreaming! "The Kindly Ones" part 3.

Loki and Puck are the kidnappers of Daniel Hall, and they put him in to the fire to break his powers. Meanwhile Dream has an encounter with the Hobgoblin and the police tells Lyta that Daniel is dead.
name: The Kindly Ones, Part 3

description: Part 2 of the 6-part 'A Season in Hell.' Lenny checks out of the Hotel Shade, but her travelling companion isn't Kathy. Shade petitions Pandora's Box for advice, but the oracle's response is more than he bargained for.
name: A Season in Hell, Part Two

description: Part 2 of 3. While a hostile alien ship bombards a Federation colony with deadly radiation, a popular uprising topples the leadership, leaving Chekov's old flame and Spock in the hands of the rebels.
name: No Compromise Part Two
Blaise of Glory; The Needs of the One

description: Part 3 of 3. Time is running out for Picard, who must find some way to return his crew's minds to their proper bodies as the mysterious orchestrator of these events is revealed.
name: Bodies of Evidence

description:
The mysterious villain from last issue has the Spear of Lono, now all he needs is the mystical gem recently uncovered at a Hawaiian archaeological dig to consolidate its power and become invincible. Superboy aims to see that doesn't happen.

Superboy finds the Scavenger who stole the Spear of Lano and haves a pitched battle in a volcano in Maui. They go there to find the mystic gem that powers the Spear. In the battle the gem is lost and that upsets Doctor Kalia who wanted it to become a superhero himself. While walking on the beach Doctor Kalia finds an unexploded ordinance that blows up in his face.
name: Remains of the Dead

description:
When Supergirl learns the horrific depths of how Luthor used her during the past year, she begins an awesome and shocking transformation to strike back!

Supergirl finds out about Lex Luthor's betrayal.
name: End of Innocence

description: Part 2 of the 4-part 'Bad Gumbo': The murderous Swamp Thing rampages through the Louisiana Bayou while Alec Holland begins a spiritual odyssey to discover who - or what - he really is. Plus, Abigail Arcane embarks on a perilous journey of her own.
name: Bad Gumbo

description: Part 6 of the 6-part ‚ÄúD.O.A.‚Äù The Legionnaires guest star as the impossible happens‚Ä¶Valor dies, setting in motion a major time paradox within the DC Universe! For without Valor, the Legion of Super-Heroes and the Legionnaires cannot exist. Now past and future begin to unravel, forming the prelude to ZERO HOUR.
name: D.O.A. Part Six: The Tyranny Of Time!

person_credits.name: Roberta Gregory
person_credits.role: writer, editor, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: In a desperate attempt to obtain the location of Kussein's secret cache of missiles, Cray and the SOG team try to take out Kussein and his henchmen in a blazing firefight!

Dragon recovers from his injuries in the hospital, where he is then suddenly attacked by SuperPatriot. Dragon is able to fend off the attack, and protect his Nurse, Ann Stevens, who is the roommate of Phyllis Deeder.

Stormwatch Prime, which consists of Nautika, Sunburst and Flashpoint, go to the Vatican where they battle against some Daemonite soldiers. Sunburst, who has had anxiety after being released from Gamorra, handles the mission and is able to save everyone by flying the bomb into the sky and absorbing the fire properties of it. Weatherman One and Synergy discuss how the Daemonites must have a plan and an unknown goal and also discuss how Stormwatch Prime is ready for active duty. Meanwhile, someone named Lord Defile, a Daemonite, is watching over Stormwatch, secretly. Someone named Timespan arrives in front of Battalion, implores his assistance, and teleport the both of them away.
This issue is a prelude to the Supreme Madness story arc. It doesn't carry the SM logo, but is included in the TPB.
name: Enemy Machine

description: A flashback to the life of Boomboy, who spent several years locked in a basement. His only source of mental stimulation was the novel 'Huckleberry Finn', which contributes to his current delusions that most of his life is like the book.

Hardcase and Choice are in Hardcase's car, headed towards the secret base of Aladdin, when they are met with Aladdin agents Foxfire, Dirt Devil and War Eagle. Head Knocker and Hardwire accompany the crew, being made temporary Aladdin agents. Hardcase immediately turns around and the Aladdin agents are bewildered that their mere presence caused the hero to surrender. However, the real reason was because Hardcase did not want another of his cars destroyed in an ultra fight. Foxfire, Dirt Devil and War Eagle chase after them and a large battle ensues. Head Knocker and Hardwire return back to the base to bide their time and strike against Hardcase and Choice at a better time. Choice and Hardcase finally defeat Foxfire, Dirt Devil and War Eagle and feel tired when they are finally met with Hardwire and Head Knocker.
name: The Angry Past: Part Two
Requiem, Part Two

description: Zip Zap saves the Strangers from impending death after they all fall off a cliff after running away from the demon lord, Bastinado. ElectroCute explains to the team that she knows the information they seek is there, but not in the immediate vicinity. She gives a general direction to where the source of information is and Zip Zap rushes through different locations to find it. He finally arrives to meet the Entity and pleads with the Entity to give him the information he needs. Zip Zap comes running back to the Strangers and brings them past Bastinado and back to Earth, telling the team that he now has the answer to their situation.
name: Detour!
Freexshow

description:
The NYPD accuses Sersi of murder, despite Black Knight‚Äôs confirmation of her innocence. In a moment of distress, will Sersi be able to control her rage? And who will be the victim is she loses all control?

Sersi's psychosis reaches a boiling point when she is accused of the murder of two innocent detectives, leaving Avengers Mansion a pile of rubble. The Avengers attempt to reign her in, but Black Knight is by her side due to the mindlink they share. When he shakes off that link for Crystal's sake, Sersi seemingly kills them all, only to then be taken by Proctor.
name: Armageddon

description: Cap is in for the fight of his life, but it may cost him much more than that. FIGHTING CHANCE is heating up!
name: Graven Images

description: System Crash strikes! The target: The Staten Island Ferry! And the Avengers taking over the rescue means Daredevil has to take his investigation "underground". Meanwhile, Captain America does some investigating of his own!
name: Tree Of Knowledge - Part 2: System Error

description: The new-look Vance Astro leads the GUARDIANS OF THE GALAXY into battle against Mephisto and Malevolence deep within The Beyonder¬¥s universe! The Guardians¬¥ absence is noticed by Mainframe and the other Galactic Guardians, who have problems of their own! Meanwhile, The Beyonder and Protege join forces in an attempt to avoid cosmic judgement! And best of all, Hollywood comes face-to-face with - tsk, tsk, almost spoiled the surprise!
name: Climb Far, Your Goal The Sky, Your Aim the Star!

description:
Overview

Hulk, the Starjammers and the Silver Surfer are taken to Lord Armageddon, Trauma's father. The intruders ask Armageddon to release Atalanta. But Trauma refuses, since he wants to web Atalanta. So a big battle is spawned. Armageddon's power measures with that of the Silver Surfer, and Hulk goes after and accidentally kills Trauma.

Trauma forgives the intruders, and lets them go. Armageddon respects his son's last wish.

Exciting conclusion to the Troyjan War!
name: The Troyjan War, Part 4: The Big Bang

description: Steel Raven and Typhoid Mary team-up to ‚Äòpunish‚Äô men who have abused their wives. Typhoid‚Äôs damaging shrink is exposed. Mary, and all her personalities, make a vow to protect the rights of women!
name: Bloody Mary part 2: Battle of the sexes

description:
The Death of Gwen Stacy as told from the perspective of Bugle reporter Phil Sheldon.

From an Epic story of the Marvel Universe, to one of the most personal. This tells the story of how Phil Sheldon met a young woman named Gwen, and she made him feel young again. Phil is investigating the Death Of Captain Stacey. Everyone says Spiderman killed the Police Captain, but Phil knows he was on the roof with Dr. Octapus, so he goes about trying to clear Spideys name.
name: The Day She Died

description:
The Stranger has to take care for the consequences of his actions.

The Earth's heroes, along the Shi'ar, Eternals and New Universe superhumans try to figure out what's happening between the cosmic entities. Meanwhile, on Earth, Kismet discover her 'family' and has to take decisions and consequently fight to save them.
name: Three Men And A Cocoon

description: Silver Surfer and Legacy must pacify the monks of the Oracle‚Äôs monastery. Will Thanos ever return what is not rightfully his? No chance! The battle for all-encompassing knowledge just got heated.
name: Escape

description:
The Surfer's return to Zenn-La is not what it seems...or is it? Reality and fantasy entwine to send the Silver Surfer on the galactic adventure of his dreams! Or his nightmares!

Summary
As payment for setting him straight, Legacy has offered the Silver Surfer an opportunity to use a machine that caters to the dreams of the client in a virtual reality in a local business. He accepts and is hooked up to the machine. His dream takes him to Zenn-La's past and he has Shalla Bal at his side. He is on one side of the bloody civil war that led to the advanced society of the future.

Norrin and Shalla return to the city of Zenn-La and meet with the leader of the enlightened Norrin Konn. Norrin forms a plan to take out the Warlord and her top generals to end the war. With him goes Shalla and 5 other soldiers.

Back back in the real world, Avatar has made her move on the Surfer while he is defenseless.
name: Princess Of Zenn-La

description: Reprints Amazing-Spider Man #12

name: New Gods For Old

description:
A special What If? issue spotlighting Phoenix and Cyclops‚Äôs relationship! What if Jean Grey and Scott Summers had married earlier? What if the two had never fallen in love? And what if Jean had chosen Wolverine over Cyclops?

Three stories in one issue centered around the wedding of Cyclops and Jean Grey.

In one story, just as Hank McCoy had decided to leave the X-Men, Cyclops and Jean Grey arrived and announced that they had decided to get married. After the wedding, Scott and Jean Summers opted to live a normal life with Scott working full-time for a radio station and Jean using her contacts in advertising. Soon after, the remaining X-Men decided to go their own ways and move on to normal lives as well. With Scott and Jean becoming famous for their book America's Opening Heart: The Growing Acceptance of Mutants in Society and the original X-Men leading their own lives, Professor X formed a new team of X-Men. Eventually, Xavier discovered an extremely powerful mutant presence on the island of Krakoa and accompanied his new X-Men to investigate it. The X-Men soon found out that Krakoa itself was the mutant and given their lack of experience, the X-Men were soon killed by Krakoa. Once Krakoa made his move into Japan, the Avengers were called in to assist Sunfire in preventing Krakoa from making it to Tokyo. The Avengers eventually destroyed Krakoa and discovered the bodies of the X-Men once it had collapsed into muck. Charles Xavier was buried with the original X-men attending his funeral.
name: X-Men Wedding Album

description: Part 1 of the 3-part 'Infestation.' The roaches are getting out of hand, beginning to murder people and causing Boogieman's rats to prepare for the worst. Meanwhile, the rest of the Blood Syndicate goes looking for a hot club...one that once found, is made too hot by a certain villain.
name: Infestation, Part 1 - Dread Luck
Sanctimony
The Winslow

volume.name: Buck Godot - Zap Gun For Hire

name: Blood And Bones, Part 3 - Thicker Than Water
The Man Who Wasn't Felix Quintero

description:
This is the issue where Tyleet conceives scouter's elf-child. Tyleet further makes frienship with a forest dwelling human, who teaches her many of his words, and establishes a treestump-altar for him to make offerings to the creatures of the forest.
Meanwhile, the modern humans have discovered the cache of crystals that have been sitting at the receded ocean, amongs heap of dirt and rubble. Wind of this discovery is discovered by the Grohmul Djun.
name: SHARDS PART THREE

description:
Omega Red is on a murderous rampage, and to stop him Cable must team up with‚Ä¶the Acolytes of Magneto!? But what is Omega Red after? And can Cable even trust the Acolytes not to betray him?

Cable joins with the Acolytes to hunt Omega Red down at the former arctic base of Magneto. Cable gets a shock, however, when he learns that the Acolytes aren't really after Omega Red.

Synopsis

Omega Red visits the research lab of Director Lashniev, home of Project Epsilon. After killing everyone but the Director, Omega Red coerces Lashniev to give him certain protocols that may stem the death spore which ravages his body. Lashniev is hesitant but finally downloads the information after getting thoroughly beaten.

Cable and a few Acolytes land a few minutes later and they are met by angry troops. The Acolytes start wasting these guards until Cable forcibly insists that they stop. Milan finds Lashniev and hooks up and sees that Omega Red was in fact just there. The Acolytes fear that Omega Red may be headed to Avalon to perform his lifesaving experiment. The only access point from Earth is at Magneto's base at the Arctic. Cable travels with the Acolytes and stakes out the base.

As the team figures how to penetrate the base, Cable takes Katu aside and asks him how he can align himself with these Acolytes. Katu explains that he was an Inuit fisherman in Russia. He had a family and lived a peaceful life. Unbeknownst to him, his mutant power of redirecting transmissions was affecting Russian satellites. An ops team arrived and wiped out Katu's family and abducted him to reconstruct his body for their purposes. This gross act instilled in Katu a sense of revenge.

The group approaches Magneto's base and reach the outer buoys. Breaching these will cause an alarm so Katu climbs one and blows it up. He uses his powers to redirect the perimeter beams elsewhere while Cable and the other Acolytes approach the base. Voght teleports the group inside and they begin to prepare for Omega Red's arrival. Cable is surprised to learn that he can open doors by simply asking. Even more surprising is when he asks for the lights to turn on that he finds Omega Red strung up. The ultimate surprise is finding that he's been ambushed by the entire Acolyte team, as led by Colossus.
name: The Killing Field, Part 2: Like Lambs to the Slaughter...

description: The Ladakh attack! When Archer learns that Master Darque has murdered everyone at the temple in Ladakh, he vows to avenge his fallen friends and teachers. He'll have to go it alone, however, thanks to the seductive powers that Pamela has developed over Armstrong. As Darque re-animates those he has slain to fight in his defense, will Archer be able to overcome an army of the undead on his own?
name: Ladakh Attack

description:
Overview

This issue introduces readers to the newest Grendel, a man known only as Jonah, who is discovered, face down in the snow and half-dead, by the workers of Ice Station Hellman. Can Jonah help these stranded workers or is he in fact the carrier of the mysterious virus causing each of them to quite literally explode?

Also in this issue: Matt Wagner's painted back-up story continues, featuring Grendel-Prime.
name: Chapter 1; Glistening Part 2

volume.name: Grendel Tales: The Devil in Our Midst

name: Strangers Among Us: Act I of IV

description: KnightQuest: The Search. Quarry, Part 1 of 3. Picking up from elements in Batman Shadow of the Bat (1992) #23, Bruce Wayne continues his relentless pursuit of the abductors of Shondra Kinsolving. Behind the abduction is Benedict Asp, a man with world-threatening plans...and sinister ties to Kinsolving's past!
name: Quarry, Part 1

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description:
1. Page part 1 (comic)
Cirin and Cerebus keep fighting, and Dave watches the fight from his drawing board.

2. Page part 2 (text)
Victor talks to the audience

3. Speech to Ozcon III Retailer Conference

4. Rare Bit Fiends (an 8 page preview by Ric Veitch)

5. Cerebus pin-up from the March 1994 cover of Exchange Magazine
name: Mothers and Daughters 31 : Page

person_credits.role: writer, penciler, letterer, inker, cover, journalist

description:
When a power core failure deactivates the security system at the mansion, Sabretooth attacks. And he has Jubilee in his sights!

Putting The Cat Out
name: Putting The Cat Out

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description:
Wolverine hallucinates, seeing himself in the Weapon X gear as Cyber breaks his bone claws. Then he realizes that he is in a car with Zoe Culloden on the run from Cyber, shortly after Cyber really did break the claws in one of Wolverine's hands. Cyber pursues them as Wolverine and Zoe try to make it to Muir Island. Meanwhile, it is revealed that Bloodscream is still alive.

Note: This comic features a number of tubes with blood-samples taken from Wolverine, one of which is labeled "X-23", the same name as Wolverine's clone X-23 (Laura Kinney). Altough the character of X-23 was not created until 2003 (and it seems unlikely that this was planned) fandom sees this as a 'concept-appearance' for X-23.
